Yesterday’s Internet outage served as a reminder of the relative vulnerability of the Internet, with content delivery network provider Fastly reporting that the problem was caused by a bug in a software update it deployed. Apple is working with two Chinese companies on the development of electric car batteries. News also emerged that the company’s newly announced Private Relay feature won’t be coming to South Africa. Eskom is set to continue load-shedding throughout the week and we have reached 50% of 2020’s total load-shedding figures. The US Department of Justice has deemed ransomware cyberattacks to be as serious a threat as terrorism is. A SpaceX competitor has raised $650 million to produce a 3D-printed rocket. Here is what is happening in the tech world today: